{"_id":"SpawnGod","name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/tentacles/tentacles-eyes-pink.webp","system":{"npcType":"creature","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["An abomination of flesh and tentacles","Obeying Arthur's will"],"gifts":[{"name":"Flesh Abomination","description":"A Spawn can perform its action with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the end of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the growth table. If not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per Scene. When the Spawn acts, roll 1 die: from 1 to 5 it will rage against one of Arthur's enemies chosen at random. On a 6, it will act against an ally or Arthur himself. If the Spawn has more actions, roll the die for each single action.\n\nGrowth Steps:\nStep 1: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Range of 12 feet\nStep 2: +1 Action - If a target fails a Defense Check, in addition to suffering 1 Wound it will be dragged towards the Spawn or thrown away\nStep 3: +1 Wound, +1 OL, Mass growth to a size of 18 cubic feet"}],"background":"Arthur Browne can tear pieces of flesh from The God Under the Mine's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. These abominations of flesh and tentacles obey Arthur's will, though they become increasingly unpredictable as they grow. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3 Spawns at once. The Spawns continue to grow and mutate throughout combat, becoming more powerful and dangerous - but also more likely to attack allies or even Arthur himself as their monstrous nature overwhelms their obedience."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"summoned-creature","creator":"arthur-browne","usage":"max-three-at-once"}}
